name: Lollo Rosso Goa

reviews.review_text:
Superb concept cafe located in the midst of farmlands. The ambience is calming and serene. The staff is attentive and helpful.

Preparations were alright but the ambience made up for that. Do try their avocado sandwich.

Highly recommended cafe if you are in Goa üèñÔ∏è

Lollo Rosso in Anjuna is a peaceful gem tucked 250m off the main road, overlooking lush paddy fields. The Turkish poached eggs and Palestinian eggplant were flavorful and beautifully prepared. Surrounded by nature, we spotted birds, a peacock, and even monkeys. Perfect for breakfast or lunch,  highly recommend for a serene and delicious experience!

Lollo Rosso is an extremely beautiful place with helpful staff and amazing food.

I went there two times - once for breakfast and once for dinner.

I had spaghetti during dinner - it was amazing.

On my breakfast trip - Tried their Eggs Benedict, and that was perhaps one of the best breakfasts I've had. Whoever cooked that hollandaise sauce has some mad cooking skills !!

The staff is very polite and helpful, much more than most restaurants I went to in Goa.
